"I'se loss my cow-brutes, Cunnel," replied the scout; "two right loikely heffers;
                  'un on 'em speckle all over, 'cept the tail, an' thet white'n yer face. Ye hain't
                  seed 'em no whar 'long the road, nohow, hes ye?"

"We are tired of the war. We are willing to give up slavery. We know it is gone;
                  but so long as our Government holds out, we must stand by it. We cannot betray it
                  and each other."
